OL,4,Cacquitted of terrorism charges
OL,6,FOne of Northern Ireland's longest-
OL,7,Frunning trials concluded with the
OL,8,Facquittal of two men charged with
OL,9,Fterrorist offences.
OL,11,FFive years after the non-jury trial
OL,12,Fcommenced, Mr Justice O'Hara returned
OL,13,F'not guilty' verdicts against Colin
OL,14,FDuffy and Henry Fitzsimons.
OL,16,FAs he delivered his judgment at
OL,17,FBelfast Crown Court, the senior judge
OL,18,Fruled that covert recordings which
OL,19,Fformed the heart of the Crown's case
OL,20,Fdid not meet the standard to secure
OL,21,Fconvictions.
